# Build: Public NFC Profile Page (`app/t/[slug]/page.js`)

## Context
Refer to CLAUDE.md for full project context, stack, folder structure, database schema, and Supabase client conventions before writing any code. This page is outside the admin and customer layouts entirely — it has no sidebar, no header bar, no navigation. It is a completely standalone page.

---

## What to build

The public-facing profile page at `app/t/[slug]/page.js`. This is what a stranger sees when they tap a Beem Hive NFC card with their phone. It must be fast, beautiful, and work flawlessly on mobile without any login.

This is a **React Server Component** — no `'use client'` directive at the top level. The tap event must be logged server-side before the page renders.

---

## Performance requirements — this is the most performance-critical page in the entire project

- **Time to first byte must be minimal** — all data fetching and tap logging happens server-side before HTML is sent to the browser
- **Minimal JavaScript** — this page should ship close to zero client-side JS. The only client-side interactions (copy button, save contact) can be isolated into small `'use client'` child components — the page shell itself stays a Server Component
- **No layout shift** — profile photo dimensions are fixed; always render the photo container at its final size with a background color placeholder before the image loads (`bg-gray-200` fallback)
- **Image optimisation** — use Next.js `<Image>` component for the profile photo with explicit `width` and `height` props. Never a raw `<img>` tag.
- **No unnecessary re-renders** — since this is a Server Component, there are no re-renders by definition. Keep it that way.

---

## Data fetching — service role client only

This page is visited by anonymous strangers. They are not logged in. RLS will block all queries from anonymous users. Use `lib/supabase/server.js` (service role client) for every Supabase call on this page.

**Step 1 — Fetch the NFC item by slug:**
```js
const { data: nfcItem } = await supabase
  .from('nfc_items')
  .select('id, is_active, owner_id, product_type')
  .eq('slug', slug)
  .single()
```

**If `nfcItem` is null** (slug doesn't exist): call Next.js `notFound()` — renders the app's 404 page.

**If `nfcItem.is_active === false`**: render the inactive card page (see below) — do not log a tap event for inactive cards.

**Step 2 — Log the tap event (active cards only):**

Before fetching the profile, log the tap. This fires server-side before the HTML is returned to the browser:

```js
// Extract device type from request headers
const userAgent = headers().get('user-agent') || ''
const isMobile = /mobile|android|iphone|ipad/i.test(userAgent)
const deviceType = isMobile ? 'mobile' : 'desktop'

// Hash the IP for deduplication — never store raw IPs
const ip = headers().get('x-forwarded-for')?.split(',')[0] || 'unknown'
const ipHash = await hashIp(ip) // see helper below

// Deduplication check — skip if same ip_hash + nfc_item_id tapped within 5 minutes
const fiveMinutesAgo = new Date(Date.now() - 5 * 60 * 1000).toISOString()
const { count } = await supabase
  .from('tap_events')
  .select('*', { count: 'exact', head: true })
  .eq('nfc_item_id', nfcItem.id)
  .eq('ip_hash', ipHash)
  .gte('created_at', fiveMinutesAgo)

if (count === 0) {
  await supabase.from('tap_events').insert({
    nfc_item_id: nfcItem.id,
    device_type: deviceType,
    referrer: headers().get('referer') || null,
    ip_hash: ipHash,
  })
}
```

**IP hash helper** — write this as a pure async function in `lib/utils.js`:
```js
export async function hashIp(ip) {
  const encoder = new TextEncoder()
  const data = encoder.encode(ip + process.env.IP_HASH_SALT)
  const hashBuffer = await crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', data)
  const hashArray = Array.from(new Uint8Array(hashBuffer))
  return hashArray.map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0')).join('').slice(0, 16)
}
```

Add `IP_HASH_SALT` to `.env.local` — any random string, e.g. `beem_hive_salt_2024`. This prevents rainbow table attacks on the hashed IPs.

**Step 3 — Fetch the profile:**
```js
const { data: profile } = await supabase
  .from('profiles')
  .select('name, title, bio, photo_url, links, show_save_contact, background')
  .eq('user_id', nfcItem.owner_id)
  .single()
```

If `profile` is null (shouldn't happen in normal operation, but defensive): render the inactive card page with the message "This profile hasn't been set up yet."

