## Active profile page

### Background

The page background uses the customer's chosen `background` value from `profiles.background`. This is either:
- A hex color: `#1a1a2e` → apply as `style={{ backgroundColor: '#1a1a2e' }}`
- A gradient string: `linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e, #16213e)` → apply as `style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(...)' }}`
- Null (not set): fall back to a default — `linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a, #1e293b)` (a deep slate gradient)

The background covers the full viewport — `min-h-screen w-full`.

Determine if the background is light or dark to set text colors appropriately. A simple heuristic: if the background value contains any of `#f`, `#e`, `#d`, `white`, or `light`, treat as light background (dark text). Otherwise treat as dark background (light text). Use this to set `text-white` vs `text-gray-900` on all text elements.

### Layout

Centered single column. `max-w-sm mx-auto px-4 py-10`. Everything stacked vertically with consistent spacing.

### Profile photo

Circular, 96px diameter. Use Next.js `<Image>` with `width={96}` `height={96}` `className="rounded-full object-cover"`. 

- If `photo_url` exists: render the image from Supabase Storage
- If null: render a fallback circle (`bg-emerald-600 rounded-full w-24 h-24`) with the customer's initial centered in white bold text

Add a subtle white ring around the circle: `ring-2 ring-white/20`

### Name, title, bio

- Name: large, bold, centered. Use the light/dark text color determined from background.
- Title: medium weight, slightly muted (white/70 on dark, gray-600 on light), centered
- Bio: small, centered, max 3 lines with `line-clamp-3`, slightly more muted. Only render if `bio` is not null/empty.

All three use `text-shadow` subtly for legibility on gradient backgrounds — apply via inline style: `textShadow: '0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)'` on dark backgrounds, none on light.

### Link buttons

Map `profile.links` array and render each as a button. Links are ordered — render in array order (the order the customer set in the profile builder).

Each link button:
- Full width, `rounded-xl`, `py-3 px-4`
- Background: `rgba(255,255,255,0.12)` on dark backgrounds, `rgba(0,0,0,0.07)` on light — a subtle frosted effect
- Border: `1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2)` on dark, `1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1)` on light
- Hover: `rgba(255,255,255,0.2)` on dark, `rgba(0,0,0,0.12)` on light — but since this is a Server Component, handle hover with a plain CSS class in a `<style>` tag or Tailwind's `hover:` variant via a thin client component wrapper
- Left: type icon (lucide-react, same icon mapping as the profile builder) + link label/type name
- Right: `ExternalLink` icon, small, muted

Map link types to display labels:
- `website` → "Website"
- `instagram` → "Instagram"
- `twitter` → "Twitter / X"
- `linkedin` → "LinkedIn"
- `whatsapp` → "WhatsApp"
- `phone` → "Phone"
- `email` → "Email"
- `custom` → use the URL domain as the label, e.g. `mysite.com` extracted with `new URL(url).hostname`

Each link button is a plain `<a href={url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">` — no onClick needed, native anchor behaviour is correct here.

If `links` is empty or null: do not render the links section at all.

### Save contact button

Only rendered if `profile.show_save_contact === true`.

A distinct button below the links — slightly different style to stand out:
- Background: `emerald-500` or `emerald-600` — solid, not frosted
- Text: white, "Save Contact"
- Left icon: `Contact` or `UserPlus` (lucide-react)
- Full width, `rounded-xl`, `py-3`

This button triggers a `.vcf` file download. Since this is a Server Component, the save contact button must be a small `'use client'` component:

**File:** `components/public/save-contact-button.js`

On click, the client component calls `GET /api/vcard?userId={owner_id}` which returns a `.vcf` file as a download.

**API route:** `app/api/vcard/route.js`

```js
// GET /api/vcard?userId={userId}
// Fetches the user's profile using service role client
// Generates a .vcf string
// Returns with headers:
//   Content-Type: text/vcard
//   Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="{name}.vcf"
```

vCard format to generate:
```
BEGIN:VCARD
VERSION:3.0
FN:{name}
TITLE:{title}
NOTE:{bio}
URL:{first website link if exists}
TEL:{phone link if exists}
EMAIL:{email link if exists}
END:VCARD
```

Only include fields that exist in the profile — omit null/empty lines.

